Ecological notes : very common in all types of woodland; ancient woodland with oak, hazel and bramble; heathland; wetlands including fens, bogs and water meadows; parkland; old hedges; unimproved grassland; near shore; gardens. Reared from nests of song thrush and moorhen. iv–xi.
